Study Title: Trial of TP Versus TC Regimens for Stage IVb, Persistent, or Recurrent Cervical Cancer (JCOG0505, CC-TPTC-P3)
Brief Summary: To evaluate the clinical benefits of Paclitaxel plus Carboplatin compared with Paclitaxel plus Cisplatin in Stage IVb, Persistent, or Recurrent Cervical Cancer
Primary Outcome Measures: overall survival, During the study conduct
Secondary Outcome Measures: progression-free survival, During the study conduct|response rate, During the study conduct|adverse events, During the study conduct|severe adverse events, During the study conduct|proportion of periods of non-hospitalization to those of the planned treatment, 18 weeks
Collaborators: Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare, Japan
Study Design: Allocation: RANDOMIZED|Intervention Model: PARALLEL|Masking: NONE|Primary Purpose: TREATMENT
